SIMPLE: burnish
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Burnish
<hw>Bur"nish</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Burnished</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Burnishing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>burnischen</ets>, <ets>burnissen</ets>, <ets>burnen</ets>, OF.
<ets>burnir</ets>, <ets>brunir</ets>, to make brown, polish, F.
<ets>brunir</ets>, fr. F. <ets>brun</ets> brown, fr. OHG.
<ets>br<?/n</ets>; cf. MHG. <ets>briunen</ets> to make brown, polish.
See <er>Brown</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>To cause to shine; to make
smooth and bright; to polish; specifically, to polish by rubbing with
something hard and smooth; <as>as, to <ex>burnish</ex> brass or
paper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The frame of <qex>burnished</qex> steel, that east a glare⟦br⟧
From far, and seemed to thaw the freezing air.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now the village windows blaze,⟦br⟧
<qex>Burnished</qex> by the setting sun.</q>
<rj><qau>Cunningham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Burnishing machine</b></col>, <cd>a machine for smoothing
and polishing by compression, as in making paper collars.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Burnish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Burnish
<hw>Bur"nish</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To shine forth; to brighten; to
become smooth and glossy, as from swelling or filling out; hence, to
grow large.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A slender poet must have time to grow,⟦br⟧
And spread and <qex>burnish</qex> as his brothers do.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My thoughts began to <qex>burnish</qex>, sprout, and swell.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Burnish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Burnish
<hw>Bur"nish</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The effect of burnishing; gloss;
brightness; luster.</def> <rj><au>Crashaw.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Burnisher</ent>⟦br⟧
